PRETORIA - Bulls lock Lood de Jager will miss the team s next Super Rugby match against the Toyota Cheetahs this weekend after suffering a concussion on his debut against the DHL Stormers last Saturday.He is in a stable condition and will follow World Rugby s Return to Play protocol and remain on the sidelines.READ: Lood de Jager cited for shoulder chargeIn other injury news, the Bulls on Wednesday updated the situation at the franchise. We are pleased to announce that three of our players on the long term injury list, Arno Botha, Jannes Kirsten and Adriaan Strauss, have resumed selected team sessions. They will not be available for selection this week, a statement said. Jan Serfontein and Martin Dreyer have resumed full training and both players will be available for selection this week.African News Agency